        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 7 at 4:28AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 428 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 8 miles southeast of Ben Bolt to near Ricardo
to Riviera Beach. Movement was east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kingsville, Driscoll, Bishop, Riviera Beach, Ricardo, Kingsville
Naval Air Station, Malaquite Beach, Petronila, Loyola Beach, and
Chapman Ranch.

This includes the following highways...
US Highway 281 near mile marker 686.
US Highway 77 between mile markers 676 and 700.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
